Jeweller Ginza Tanaka on Tuesday showcased the 15kg sculpture, which has been commissioned to mark the 40th anniversary this year of the release of Star Wars.The mask will be available for purchase on May the fourth a date known among fans as Star Wars Day because of its similarity to one of the franchise's most famous lines: "May the Force be with you".The jeweller also plans to release gold coins specially designed to celebrate the anniversary in the more affordable price range of $1,200 to $11,000 (about R15,9k to R145,9k).Ginza Tanaka, which is celebrating its 125th anniversary this year, has in the past created other gold commemorative products including a Christmas tree, samurai helmets and a replica of footballer Lionel Messi's left foot.